## URL Pattern
Card detail pages follow this pattern:
```
https://www.ctbcbank.com/content/twrbo/zh_tw/cc_index/cc_product/cc_introduction_index/{SLUG}.html
```

The slug can be extracted from any CTBC card URL — e.g. `B_Cashback_Signature` from the URL above.

## Post-Extraction Steps

After extraction, import to DB and optionally sync to Supabase:
```bash
cd cardsense-extractor && uv run python import_jsonl_to_db.py outputs/ctbc-targeted-{timestamp}.jsonl
```

To verify results:
```python
import json
with open('outputs/ctbc-targeted-{timestamp}.jsonl', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:
    promos = [json.loads(line) for line in f if line.strip()]
print(f'Total: {len(promos)}')
from collections import Counter
print(Counter(p['cardName'] for p in promos))
```

## Additional Benefits Page
The CTBC additional benefits page (`cc_add_index.html`) contains service-type perks (airport lounge, parking, roadside assistance) — these are card features, not cashback promotions, and are NOT extracted by this pipeline.

## Key Files
- `extractor/ctbc_real.py` — Main extractor (card listing, page parsing, promotion normalization)
- `jobs/run_ctbc_real_job.py` — Full extraction job runner
- `jobs/run_ctbc_targeted.py` — Targeted extraction job runner
- `jobs/run_real_bank_job.py` — Shared job runner framework
